programmes.show_description: A baby monitor picks up a ghostly figure walking next to a child's bed and a young woman ushers in the new year with an undeniable sign from her late father. (S8, ep 8)
Hook Island Monster, Skydivers' Plane Stall, and Somalia Freighter Phantom: The team explore possible proof of a sea monster, a tale of a skydive gone wrong, and a ghostly image. (S3, ep 8)
Panama UFO Disc, Bloody Red Sea, and the Dyatlov Pass Incident: The team examine a strange UFO sighting, the sudden appearance of a red sea and possible proof of a Yeti. (S3, ep 9)
Orb & Crash Debris, KGB UFOs and Aliens, and Superhuman reflexes: Is the strange silver orb in the sky a UFO? And is an infamous spy organisation's footage of aliens real? (S4, ep 4)
Cork: Dublin dealer Ian Dowling and his mate Butzy go in search of Irish treasures, finding a mysterious stone head, a strange carving and a much-loved gadget from the 60s. (S1, ep 1)
Kerry: Dealer Ian Dowling is off to County Kerry. He meets celebrity dolphin Fungi and calls in at Dingle's Curran's pub. But is there any treasure to be found? (S1, ep 2)
Huddersfield 4: Join David Dickinson as more collectors try to sell their items to dealers. Will they strike a deal, or will they take a chance at auction instead? (S10, ep 70)
Sheldon and Scott embark on a coast-to-coast scavenge. It's not just about money, it's about the thrill of the hunt and a passion for the past. (S3, ep 6)
Henry Cole chances his arm at a high class auction of vintage petroliana. (S2, ep 2)
In Pain in the Membrane: Ivy's locker shines some light on the business, while Lisa learns that she needs her locker about as much as she needs a hole in her head. (S14, ep 5)
How the West Covina Was Won: Lisa makes a big mistake as she's too busy looking back. Meanwhile, Rene gets his hands on a bargain and makes the most of it. (S14, ep 6)
Burmese or Busted?: Les gets excited over a jar of powdered gold. He believes it's worth thousands. But is it valuable or just eyeshadow? An explosive acid test reveals all. (S7, ep 9)
Lawyer Up Son: The shop lands itself in trouble when a customer calls in their lawyer to settle a huge row over a fake receipt. Fortunately, Les has a trick up his sleeve. (S7, ep 10)
Wanted: Pawn Or Alive: Rick's taste for football is wetted when a bucket hat lands at the shop. Spencer provides an Incredible Hulk comic book, capturing Corey's imagination.
Hidden Flaws: When a DC-10 aeroplane explodes mid-flight over Iowa, the quick-thinking pilot saves 184 passengers. But what caused such a huge disaster? (5 of 6)
Man vs Machine: When a Boeing 777 crashes into San Francisco Airport with no warning, engineers race to figure out what could have caused such a disaster. (6 of 6)

Texan farm workers are confronted by a 200-foot long object in the sky in 1957. In 1979, a UFO releases spiked spheres that leave a man unconscious in Scotland. (S2, ep 7)

Siberian Death Mask: A 1700-year-old death mask from Siberia reveals ancient cranial surgery, shedding light on advanced medical practices of the Tashtyk culture. (S4, ep 8)
CIA Mind Control: Declassified: Explore some of the darker elements of the MK Ultra programme, which sought out a miracle mind control method via human experimentation. (S7, ep 7)
Entertainment: Examine the influence that popular culture and entertainment have on daily life. As we gravitate to larger-than-life stories, outlandish myths begin to spread. (S1, ep 2)
In 1968, airmen in North Dakota spot a huge UFO over one of the US' most high security Air Force bases. Papua New Guinea village locals report strange objects in the sky in 1959. (S2, ep 5)
In 2000, two brothers spot a UFO the size of six football fields after a hunting in Idaho. A Madagascan city is plunged into darkness when a metal craft hovers overhead in 1954. (S2, ep 6)

A father and son see mysterious lights near their property and call the sheriff's office. A large craft covers a French town in an odd material. (S2, ep 9)
